Defendant Johnny Deval Combs in court with attorney Debra J Patterson.  Defendant Johnny Deval Combs in custody.  Deann L Heard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 

The Court imposed the following sentence:
Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 7 years.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 3 years   with credit for 52 days time served.  Defendant shall serve 4 years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.    The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program, but not for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 
 * Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample.
 * Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable surcharges, costs and disbursements, from prison funds not to exceed 25%.  Balance to be paid while on extended supervision.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - Undergo a mental health evaluation and follow any treatment regimen recommended;
 - Remain controlled substance free other than those legally prescribed for defendant by a duly licensed physician for his mental or physical well-being and for only as long as deemed medically necessary;
 - Remain alcohol free;
 - AODA assessment and treatment;
 - Urine screens;
 - No contact with Sheikh U.;
 - No contact with Real Deal Convenience Store located at 1412 North 27th Street, in the city and county of Milwaukee, Wisconsin;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Parenting classes;
 - Pay the balance remaining of the costs, surcharges and disbursements.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.  

Court set restitution at zero as nothing has been filed by the victim, but will hold open same for 60 days of today's date should the victim request same.

